></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 215<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/21/03 2:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: lvl 60 (almost) and tanking in T2</span><hr size=1> I tank fine in tier 3, and my gear is far from uber.  it takes agro management, placement, and grouping with intelligent people.  but it can be done. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=476715">Veda Kai'Rin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/21/03 10:00 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: lvl 60 (almost) and tanking in T2</span><hr size=1> You'll be fine at 60, but good luck finding a group.  There are a lot of other tanks who are 61+ LFG, both knights and warriors.  But if you can find a group, then you'll be fine. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124485">Deterious</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daxos92>Daxos92</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/03 6:06 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: lvl 60 (almost) and tanking in T2</span><hr size=1> Raun hit the nail on the head. The hard part is lfg.<br>
<br>
Depending on your weapons, aggro can be a real bitch from 60-62 in valor. You'll notice pretty big jumps in the success rate of your taunts at 63, 64 and 65 for that zone, as you begin to be equal and above the level of the golems / razorfiends. I went through that area with a Wavecrasher and Frostbringer as my aggro setup, and always had the best aggro-boosting buffs I could find in my groups. (For shamans, the dex from focus helped quite a lot, or from chanters, Trickster's Augmentation was my friend. Rarely needed visage). <br>
<br>
One more thing, if you haven't started keeping a /shield hotkey handy, do so now. I'm surprised how many people in PoV are surprised that I use that skill so often in my groups, but literally any time a chanter has to tash before slow, or a shaman gets a slow resist, if my first Taunt fails I don't hesitate to target the debuffer, get on top of them and /shield. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 206<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/03 2:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: lvl 60 (almost) and tanking in T2</span><hr size=1> Nothing is hard to tank if it's slowed in tier 2 planes, and conversely everything is too hard for your average warrior to tank if it remains unslowed for extended amount of time.<br>
<br>
The biggest problem are getting aggro since Taunt does depend on level, and trying to convince people to take you over a level 65 tank LFG. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emilyee>Emilyee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/03 6:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: lvl 60 (almost) and tanking in T2</span><hr size=1> thanks for the info guy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
im not sure the LFG part will be to hard, most the time i come rdy with a 61 cleric 62 chanter and a 62 monk, and we just plug in a melee and what ever <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ninaor@thesteelwarrior>Ninaor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/03 11:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Valor tanking...</span><hr size=1> I'm level 61 with about 1210 AC and 5400 HP buffed with shaman / cleric spells.  My wife is a 62 cleric and we tried dou'ing yard trash in PoV at zone in.<br>
<br>
With me hacking away with Windblade and her proc'ing with that blessed hammer we were able to take down a larvae and get some fairly decent exp.  Only one problem - she used nearly 3000 mana keeping me healed.  The yard trash is level 59 and hit me for a max of like 434.<br>
<br>
Now most 61 warriors have closer to 1400 AC so this might be a bad example but I'm just trying to give you a baseline to start from <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
~Ninaor<br>
<br>
p.s.  I have no AA's yet<br>
